The recipe in the reddit post contains vanilla swirl at 4% &#xD;
was this a concious decision to leave it out here or was it just forgotten?&#xD;
Maybe update recipe or description on why you left it out here

The bilberry and blueberry make for a dark fruity body that is the core of this flavor. The cactus actually packs a punch here, first time i've come across this flavor being used prominently as opposed to just for the juiciness. The icy chill works well here, as does that little touch of blood orange for contrast. For me though, the dragonfruit and the bit of sweetener are what make this work brilliantly. The former adds a tiny tropical vibe to go with that blood orange, and a ton of juiciness, but it's the sweetener at this amount...in addition to making it all just pop, it adds just enough sweetness to keep me coming back to this dark, rich, slightly painful but in the right way juice.&#xD;
&#xD;
It really tells the story you're gunning for here. I think i'm in love with this stuff. Will definitely be making more.
